        12 November 2021 - 18 November 2021

        The Official Singles Chart Top 100 reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1. View the biggest songs of 2025.

        WEEKLY CHART REVIEW (11/11/2021 – 17/11/2021)

        🔴 (Negative)

        1) ‘Coming For You’ went up a few places! Honestly, I’m just more disappointed than I am angry at this point. Thankfully, there’ll be a huge surge in holiday music soon which will hopefully kill of the momentum for this before it gets any kind of run inside the Top 10! Unfortunately, I get the feeling that it might have a second wind as we go into 2022, but that’s a bridge we’ll cross when we come to it.

        2) ‘Mafia’ sneaked in as the second Travis Scott song! I felt that the production seemed very hollow on this, Travis Scott sounds way less engaged & hyped than he normally does, while his somewhat monotonic chanting in the ad-libs kills the vibe of this any further. I normally don’t mind the heavy use of autotune either, but it’s really being overused here! It leaves me with no real reason to revisit this sadly.

        3) ‘24/5’ falling a few places this week! Britain, why are you letting this tank? It doesn’t deserve it!

        🟠 (Mixed)

        1) ‘Flowers [Say My Name]’ is the highest debut of the week! I’m honestly not too sure where I sit with this one. I can hear where ArrDee is a competent MC, but I’m not sure really sure if that reflects on his rapping skills here! Much to my surprise, the samples of ‘Say My Name’ by Destiny’s Child & ‘Flowers’ by Sweet Female Attitude are interpolated as well as they can over a drill beat. I think I’d like this a lot more if it was by a different rapper though, because this is far from ArrDee’s best performance!

        2) ‘Escape Plan’ entered the chart & I honestly don’t even feel comfortable fully reviewing this one given the background behind what happened last week! I mean, it’s decent overall with the more haunting production & much tighter flow from Travis Scott, but this doesn’t sit at all well with me when you look into everything that happened last Friday at his Astroworld Festival, but that’s a discussion we can have in the replies if anyone wants to discuss it. RIP to the nine people who tragically lost their lives at it though! 🙏

        3) ‘No Love’ is here! I’m really surprised that Summer Walker didn’t have more of a presence in this week’s chart, especially how well she was doing on the Apple Music charts all weekend. That being said, I can definitely see why if any song of hers was going to make a splash in the Top 40, it would be this one! The romantic R&B vibe relaxes me a lot, even if the lyrics are incredibly raunchy. For as much as I think Summer Walker is incredibly underrated, SZA definitely carries this slow jam for me! I don’t see it sticking around sadly, but I hope I’m proven wrong, because I could see this growing on me enough for it to become a future positive section contender.

        4) ‘Sad Girlz Luv Money’ made it! Honestly, I can tolerate this a lot more than I should. Sure, the vocals are screechy & the production is incredibly basic, but the voices are layering in a way over the bubbly beat to the point where the whole mood of the song feels kind of elevated! I also repeat the content of how women in today’s society should have full independence in what they do & the chemistry between the two acts in somewhat convincing too. Yeah, this turned out a lot better than expected! I wouldn’t say I love it exactly, but I completely understand the appeal here.

        5) ‘Out Out’ gets placed on ACR! For as much as I like Joel Corry, this is definitely one of his weakest singles. It had a really solid run anyway, so I’m not that bothered about it crashing in this new chart!

        6) ‘Voyage’ debuted at #1 on the albums chart with the biggest opening week of 2021 so far! Again, it’s good to see ABBA finally back making music together after nearly 40 years, but this is nowhere near as good as some of their 70’s classics.

        🟢 (Positive)

        1) ‘Easy On Me’ somehow pulls back yet again to spend a fourth consecutive week at #1! Interestingly, this is also the second week in a row where it’s ended up retaining despite an Ed song leading in the mid-week update.

        2) ‘Drive’ is officially a Top 20 hit! This has an undeniably warm groove to it that just keeps me coming back to it almost every single day.

        3) ‘I Wish’ also made it into the region! Okay, I’m even more fine with ‘Out Out’ being pushed out if it means that this gains some traction instead. This is so much better in my opinion!

        4) ‘One Right Now’ is here & man, The Weeknd’s really been on a roll with his 80’s pop anthems, hasn’t he? I absolutely love the tight synths combined the shimmering reverbs give this is a somewhat nostalgic feel back to the disco days from a few decades ago, even though this song only came out last week! It also has to be among one of Post Malone’s consistently solid vocal performances. That hook is an absolute earworm too & I think it could’ve been my new obsession of the week if a certain album hadn’t dropped today, but we’ll get into that in another post.

        5) ‘Seventeen Going Under’ not took a massive jump this week, but it’s at a new peak! Does anyone know why it’s back? I don’t recall it getting an ACR reset! So happy about it regardless though, haha.

        6) ‘Smokin Out The Window’ charts higher than I personally would’ve expected! Funnily enough, while critics will look to ‘Leave The Door Open’ & ‘Skate’ as the classy Silk Sonic hits that show how well Bruno Mars & Anderson .Paak work together, I actually feel more intrigued by this one. What interests me is that both singers have enough smoothness & pristine in their voices to make this sound like a love song, even though the content is actually about finding that a former lover has been sleeping around with multiple people, therefore causing you to stress smoke! That, along with the 70’s funk instrumentation, turns an otherwise bad situation into something a fair bit more uplifting. I’m actually curious to check out their new album to came out today, because this got me very interested to see what else they’re capable of together!

        7) ‘Better Days’ (NEIKED) moved up again! I wasn’t expecting it given how many new entries there were this week, but it’s my favourite EDM song right now, so I’ll definitely take even a climb of one place for this.

        8) ‘Do It To It’ cracked the Top 40! It was a big ask trying to match the level of quality from the 2006 R&B original by female group Cherish, but Acraze somehow managed to do it! I love how the beat is perfectly synchronised with the catchy vocal hook, along with the pulsing bassline & bopping drums that hit exactly at the right over the drop. A lot of big DJ’s have been hyping this up at their sets over the summer & honestly, given how it’s impossible not to sing or dance along to this, I can see why, because this is a banger!

        9) ‘Red [Taylor’s Version]’ was released today & honestly, I’ve got plenty more to say about it in another post, but right now, I’m still too overwhelmed by the insane quality on it to even do a long piece of commentary of it! All I’m going to say is, if you haven’t already, check it out. It might effectively be a double album with 30 tracks on it & a running time of over two hours, but trust me, it’s worth it!

        My latest personal chart (replace the * with an “o”): www.crownnote.c*m/charts/piran/pirans-top-50-14

        P.S. Sorry if my analysis of the songs was a bit blunt today! I had a very busy week with work & a lot going on personally, but just let me know if you’d like me to elaborate on anything here & I’ll try to give more of an explanation over the weekend. :)
